===Adjective===
'''nice''' ({{compar}} '''[[nicer]]''', {{superl}} '''[[nicest]]''')

#Of a thing or person, easy to like.
#Of a thing or person, pleasant to look at.
#Having a pleasant taste or aroma.
#:''This fish is nice.''
#:''Your perfume smells nice.''
#[[show|Showing]] or [[require|requiring]] [[great]] [[precision]] or [[sensitive]] [[discern]]ment; [[subtle]]
#:''a '''nice''' distinction''

Often used to mean other things by people who are not nice.

====Synonyms====
*(''easy to like: person''): [[charming]], [[delightful]], [[lovely]], [[pleasant]], [[sweet]]
*(''easy to like: thing''): [[charming]], [[delightful]], [[lovely]], [[pleasant]]
*(''having a pleasant taste or aroma''): [[appetising]]/[[appetizing]], [[delicious]], [[moreish]] (''informal''), [[scrummy]] (''slang''), [[scrumptious]] (''slang''), [[tasty]]
*(''subtle''): [[fine]], [[subtle]]

====Antonyms====
